
[1]heterodox

   HET'ERODOX, a. [Gr. another, different, and opinion.]

   1. In theology, heretical; contrary to the faith and doctrines of the
   true church; or more precisely, contrary to the real doctrines of the
   Scriptures; as a heterodox opinion; opposed to orthodox.

   2. Repugnant to the doctrines or tenets of any established church.

   3. Holding opinions repugnant to the doctrines of the Scriptures, as a
   heterodox divine; or holding opinions contrary to those of an
   established church.
